* Allen Maldonado as [[Fletcher Heggs (Earth-199999)|Fletcher Heggs]]
[[wikipedia:Crystal the Monkey|Crystal the Monkey]] appears as a monkey drinking Vodka in Trevor's CBS pilot ''Caged Heat''.

| Notes                   = * This Marvel One-Shot was released alongside the DVD/Blu-Ray for ''[[Thor: The Dark World]]''.
| Trivia                  = * [[Seagate Prison]] is the same facility where [[Luke Cage (Earth-199999)|Luke Cage]] was wrongly imprisoned, which would later be shown in a flashback on the Netflix show ''[[Marvel's Luke Cage]]''.{{r|Marvel's Luke Cage Season 1 4}}
* The name of Trevor Slattery's 80's crime show ''Caged Heat'' was the working title, and distribution alias, for ''[[Iron Man 3 (film)|Iron Man 3]]''.
* One of the actors credited in the ''Caged Heat'' pilot is named after [[w:c:avp:Rick Hawkins|Rick Hawkins]], the character ''Iron Man 3'' director Shane Black portrayed in the 1987 film ''[[w:c:avp:Predator (film)|Predator]]''.
* The tracksuit criminals who appeared in the ''Caged Heat'' footage were based off [[Hawkeye Vol 4|Hawkeye]]'s "[[Tracksuit Mafia (Earth-616)|Tracksuit Mafia]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/mrdrewpearce/status/438372697685258241|title=Clearly the #AllHailTheKing tracksuit vampires cameo is a thank-you to @mattfraction for letting us crib so many of his ideas in Iron Man 3.|last=Pearce|first=Drew|date=25 February 2014|accessdate=26 February 2014}}</ref>
